30// Use this rtt if no value has been reported.
31static const int64_t kDefaultRtt = 200;

33typedef std::pair<uint32_t, VCMFrameBuffer*> FrameListPair;
34
35bool IsKeyFrame(FrameListPair pair) {
36 return pair.second->FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
37}
38
39bool HasNonEmptyState(FrameListPair pair) {
40 return pair.second->GetState() != kStateEmpty;
41}
42
43void FrameList::InsertFrame(VCMFrameBuffer* frame) {
44 insert(rbegin().base(), FrameListPair(frame->Timestamp(), frame));
45}
46
47VCMFrameBuffer* FrameList::PopFrame(uint32_t timestamp) {
48 FrameList::iterator it = find(timestamp);
49 if (it == end())
50 return NULL;
51 VCMFrameBuffer* frame = it->second;
52 erase(it);
53 return frame;
54}
55
56VCMFrameBuffer* FrameList::Front() const {
57 return begin()->second;
58}
59
60VCMFrameBuffer* FrameList::Back() const {
61 return rbegin()->second;
62}
63
64int FrameList::RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame(FrameList::iterator* key_frame_it,
65 UnorderedFrameList* free_frames) {
66 int drop_count = 0;
67 FrameList::iterator it = begin();
68 while (!empty()) {
69 // Throw at least one frame.
70 it->second->Reset();
71 free_frames->push_back(it->second);
72 erase(it++);
73 ++drop_count;
74 if (it != end() &&
75 it->second->FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
76 *key_frame_it = it;
77 return drop_count;
78 }
79 }
80 *key_frame_it = end();
81 return drop_count;
82}
83
84void FrameList::CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames(VCMDecodingState* decoding_state,
85 UnorderedFrameList* free_frames) {
86 while (!empty()) {
87 VCMFrameBuffer* oldest_frame = Front();
88 bool remove_frame = false;
89 if (oldest_frame->GetState() == kStateEmpty && size() > 1) {
90 // This frame is empty, try to update the last decoded state and drop it
91 // if successful.
92 remove_frame = decoding_state->UpdateEmptyFrame(oldest_frame);
93 } else {
94 remove_frame = decoding_state->IsOldFrame(oldest_frame);
95 }
96 if (!remove_frame) {
97 break;
98 }
99 free_frames->push_back(oldest_frame);
100 erase(begin());
101 }
102}
103
104void FrameList::Reset(UnorderedFrameList* free_frames) {
105 while (!empty()) {
106 begin()->second->Reset();
107 free_frames->push_back(begin()->second);
108 erase(begin());
109 }
110}

112VCMJitterBuffer::VCMJitterBuffer(Clock* clock,
113 std::unique_ptr<EventWrapper> event)
114 : clock_(clock),
115 running_(false),
116 frame_event_(std::move(event)),
117 max_number_of_frames_(kStartNumberOfFrames),
118 free_frames_(),
119 decodable_frames_(),
120 incomplete_frames_(),
121 last_decoded_state_(),
122 first_packet_since_reset_(true),
123 num_consecutive_old_packets_(0),
124 num_packets_(0),
125 num_duplicated_packets_(0),
126 jitter_estimate_(clock),
127 inter_frame_delay_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
128 missing_sequence_numbers_(SequenceNumberLessThan()),
129 latest_received_sequence_number_(0),
130 max_nack_list_size_(0),
131 max_packet_age_to_nack_(0),
132 max_incomplete_time_ms_(0),
133 average_packets_per_frame_(0.0f),
134 frame_counter_(0) {
135 for (int i = 0; i < kStartNumberOfFrames; i++)
136 free_frames_.push_back(new VCMFrameBuffer());
137}
138
139VCMJitterBuffer::~VCMJitterBuffer() {
140 Stop();
141 for (UnorderedFrameList::iterator it = free_frames_.begin();
142 it != free_frames_.end(); ++it) {
143 delete *it;
144 }
145 for (FrameList::iterator it = incomplete_frames_.begin();
146 it != incomplete_frames_.end(); ++it) {
147 delete it->second;
148 }
149 for (FrameList::iterator it = decodable_frames_.begin();
150 it != decodable_frames_.end(); ++it) {
151 delete it->second;
152 }
153}
154
155void VCMJitterBuffer::Start() {
156 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
157 running_ = true;
158
159 num_consecutive_old_packets_ = 0;
160 num_packets_ = 0;
161 num_duplicated_packets_ = 0;
162
163 // Start in a non-signaled state.
164 waiting_for_completion_.frame_size = 0;
165 waiting_for_completion_.timestamp = 0;
166 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time = -1;
167 first_packet_since_reset_ = true;
168 last_decoded_state_.Reset();
169
170 decodable_frames_.Reset(&free_frames_);
171 incomplete_frames_.Reset(&free_frames_);
172}
173
174void VCMJitterBuffer::Stop() {
175 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
176 running_ = false;
177 last_decoded_state_.Reset();
178
179 // Make sure we wake up any threads waiting on these events.
180 frame_event_->Set();
181}
182
183bool VCMJitterBuffer::Running() const {
184 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
185 return running_;
186}
187
188void VCMJitterBuffer::Flush() {
189 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
190 decodable_frames_.Reset(&free_frames_);
191 incomplete_frames_.Reset(&free_frames_);
192 last_decoded_state_.Reset(); // TODO(mikhal): sync reset.
193 num_consecutive_old_packets_ = 0;
194 // Also reset the jitter and delay estimates
195 jitter_estimate_.Reset();
196 inter_frame_delay_.Reset(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
197 waiting_for_completion_.frame_size = 0;
198 waiting_for_completion_.timestamp = 0;
199 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time = -1;
200 first_packet_since_reset_ = true;
201 missing_sequence_numbers_.clear();
202}

209int VCMJitterBuffer::num_duplicated_packets() const {
210 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
211 return num_duplicated_packets_;

214// Returns immediately or a |max_wait_time_ms| ms event hang waiting for a
215// complete frame, |max_wait_time_ms| decided by caller.
216VCMEncodedFrame* VCMJitterBuffer::NextCompleteFrame(uint32_t max_wait_time_ms) {
217 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
218 if (!running_) {
219 return nullptr;
220 }
221 CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames();
222
223 if (decodable_frames_.empty() ||
224 decodable_frames_.Front()->GetState() != kStateComplete) {
225 const int64_t end_wait_time_ms =
226 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() + max_wait_time_ms;
227 int64_t wait_time_ms = max_wait_time_ms;
228 while (wait_time_ms > 0) {
229 mutex_.Unlock();
230 const EventTypeWrapper ret =
231 frame_event_->Wait(static_cast<uint32_t>(wait_time_ms));
232 mutex_.Lock();
233 if (ret == kEventSignaled) {
234 // Are we shutting down the jitter buffer?
235 if (!running_) {
236 return nullptr;
237 }
238 // Finding oldest frame ready for decoder.
239 CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames();
240 if (decodable_frames_.empty() ||
241 decodable_frames_.Front()->GetState() != kStateComplete) {
242 wait_time_ms = end_wait_time_ms - clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
243 } else {
244 break;
245 }
246 } else {
247 break;
248 }
249 }
250 }
251 if (decodable_frames_.empty() ||
252 decodable_frames_.Front()->GetState() != kStateComplete) {
253 return nullptr;
254 }
255 return decodable_frames_.Front();
256}
257
258VCMEncodedFrame* VCMJitterBuffer::ExtractAndSetDecode(uint32_t timestamp) {
259 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
260 if (!running_) {
261 return NULL;
262 }
263 // Extract the frame with the desired timestamp.
264 VCMFrameBuffer* frame = decodable_frames_.PopFrame(timestamp);
265 bool continuous = true;
266 if (!frame) {
267 frame = incomplete_frames_.PopFrame(timestamp);
268 if (frame)
269 continuous = last_decoded_state_.ContinuousFrame(frame);
270 else
271 return NULL;
272 }
273 // Frame pulled out from jitter buffer, update the jitter estimate.
274 const bool retransmitted = (frame->GetNackCount() > 0);
275 if (retransmitted) {
276 jitter_estimate_.FrameNacked();
277 } else if (frame->size() > 0) {
278 // Ignore retransmitted and empty frames.
279 if (waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time >= 0) {
280 UpdateJitterEstimate(waiting_for_completion_, true);
281 }
282 if (frame->GetState() == kStateComplete) {
283 UpdateJitterEstimate(*frame, false);
284 } else {
285 // Wait for this one to get complete.
286 waiting_for_completion_.frame_size = frame->size();
287 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time = frame->LatestPacketTimeMs();
288 waiting_for_completion_.timestamp = frame->Timestamp();
289 }
290 }
291
292 // The state must be changed to decoding before cleaning up zero sized
293 // frames to avoid empty frames being cleaned up and then given to the
294 // decoder. Propagates the missing_frame bit.
295 frame->PrepareForDecode(continuous);
296
297 // We have a frame - update the last decoded state and nack list.
298 last_decoded_state_.SetState(frame);
299 DropPacketsFromNackList(last_decoded_state_.sequence_num());
300
301 UpdateAveragePacketsPerFrame(frame->NumPackets());
302
303 return frame;
304}
305
306// Release frame when done with decoding. Should never be used to release
307// frames from within the jitter buffer.
308void VCMJitterBuffer::ReleaseFrame(VCMEncodedFrame* frame) {
309 RTC_CHECK(frame != nullptr);
310 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
311 VCMFrameBuffer* frame_buffer = static_cast<VCMFrameBuffer*>(frame);
312 RecycleFrameBuffer(frame_buffer);
313}
314
315// Gets frame to use for this timestamp. If no match, get empty frame.
316VCMFrameBufferEnum VCMJitterBuffer::GetFrame(const VCMPacket& packet,
317 VCMFrameBuffer** frame,
318 FrameList** frame_list) {
319 *frame = incomplete_frames_.PopFrame(packet.timestamp);
320 if (*frame != NULL) {
321 *frame_list = &incomplete_frames_;
322 return kNoError;
323 }
324 *frame = decodable_frames_.PopFrame(packet.timestamp);
325 if (*frame != NULL) {
326 *frame_list = &decodable_frames_;
327 return kNoError;
328 }
329
330 *frame_list = NULL;
331 // No match, return empty frame.
332 *frame = GetEmptyFrame();
333 if (*frame == NULL) {
334 // No free frame! Try to reclaim some...
335 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unable to get empty frame; Recycling.";
336 bool found_key_frame = RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame();
337 *frame = GetEmptyFrame();
338 RTC_CHECK(*frame);
339 if (!found_key_frame) {
340 RecycleFrameBuffer(*frame);
341 return kFlushIndicator;
342 }
343 }
344 (*frame)->Reset();
345 return kNoError;
346}
347
348int64_t VCMJitterBuffer::LastPacketTime(const VCMEncodedFrame* frame,
349 bool* retransmitted) const {
350 assert(retransmitted);
351 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
352 const VCMFrameBuffer* frame_buffer =
353 static_cast<const VCMFrameBuffer*>(frame);
354 *retransmitted = (frame_buffer->GetNackCount() > 0);
355 return frame_buffer->LatestPacketTimeMs();
356}
357
358VCMFrameBufferEnum VCMJitterBuffer::InsertPacket(const VCMPacket& packet,
359 bool* retransmitted) {
360 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
361
362 ++num_packets_;
363 // Does this packet belong to an old frame?
364 if (last_decoded_state_.IsOldPacket(&packet)) {
365 // Account only for media packets.
366 if (packet.sizeBytes > 0) {
367 num_consecutive_old_packets_++;
368 }
369 // Update last decoded sequence number if the packet arrived late and
370 // belongs to a frame with a timestamp equal to the last decoded
371 // timestamp.
372 last_decoded_state_.UpdateOldPacket(&packet);
373 DropPacketsFromNackList(last_decoded_state_.sequence_num());
374
375 // Also see if this old packet made more incomplete frames continuous.
376 FindAndInsertContinuousFramesWithState(last_decoded_state_);
377
378 if (num_consecutive_old_packets_ > kMaxConsecutiveOldPackets) {
379 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
380 << num_consecutive_old_packets_
381 << " consecutive old packets received. Flushing the jitter buffer.";
382 Flush();
383 return kFlushIndicator;
384 }
385 return kOldPacket;
386 }
387
388 num_consecutive_old_packets_ = 0;
389
390 VCMFrameBuffer* frame;
391 FrameList* frame_list;
392 const VCMFrameBufferEnum error = GetFrame(packet, &frame, &frame_list);
393 if (error != kNoError)
394 return error;
395
396 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
397 // We are keeping track of the first and latest seq numbers, and
398 // the number of wraps to be able to calculate how many packets we expect.
399 if (first_packet_since_reset_) {
400 // Now it's time to start estimating jitter
401 // reset the delay estimate.
402 inter_frame_delay_.Reset(now_ms);
403 }
404
405 // Empty packets may bias the jitter estimate (lacking size component),
406 // therefore don't let empty packet trigger the following updates:
407 if (packet.video_header.frame_type != VideoFrameType::kEmptyFrame) {
408 if (waiting_for_completion_.timestamp == packet.timestamp) {
409 // This can get bad if we have a lot of duplicate packets,
410 // we will then count some packet multiple times.
411 waiting_for_completion_.frame_size += packet.sizeBytes;
412 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time = now_ms;
413 } else if (waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time >= 0 &&
414 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time + 2000 <= now_ms) {
415 // A packet should never be more than two seconds late
416 UpdateJitterEstimate(waiting_for_completion_, true);
417 waiting_for_completion_.latest_packet_time = -1;
418 waiting_for_completion_.frame_size = 0;
419 waiting_for_completion_.timestamp = 0;
420 }
421 }
422
423 VCMFrameBufferStateEnum previous_state = frame->GetState();
424 // Insert packet.
425 FrameData frame_data;
426 frame_data.rtt_ms = kDefaultRtt;
427 frame_data.rolling_average_packets_per_frame = average_packets_per_frame_;
428 VCMFrameBufferEnum buffer_state =
429 frame->InsertPacket(packet, now_ms, frame_data);
430
431 if (buffer_state > 0) {
432 if (first_packet_since_reset_) {
433 latest_received_sequence_number_ = packet.seqNum;
434 first_packet_since_reset_ = false;
435 } else {
436 if (IsPacketRetransmitted(packet)) {
437 frame->IncrementNackCount();
438 }
439 if (!UpdateNackList(packet.seqNum) &&
440 packet.video_header.frame_type != VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
441 buffer_state = kFlushIndicator;
442 }
443
444 latest_received_sequence_number_ =
445 LatestSequenceNumber(latest_received_sequence_number_, packet.seqNum);
446 }
447 }
448
449 // Is the frame already in the decodable list?
450 bool continuous = IsContinuous(*frame);
451 switch (buffer_state) {
452 case kGeneralError:
453 case kTimeStampError:
454 case kSizeError: {
455 RecycleFrameBuffer(frame);
456 break;
457 }
458 case kCompleteSession: {
459 if (previous_state != kStateComplete) {
460 if (continuous) {
461 // Signal that we have a complete session.
462 frame_event_->Set();
463 }
464 }
465
466 *retransmitted = (frame->GetNackCount() > 0);
467 if (continuous) {
468 decodable_frames_.InsertFrame(frame);
469 FindAndInsertContinuousFrames(*frame);
470 } else {
471 incomplete_frames_.InsertFrame(frame);
472 }
473 break;
474 }
475 case kIncomplete: {
476 if (frame->GetState() == kStateEmpty &&
477 last_decoded_state_.UpdateEmptyFrame(frame)) {
478 RecycleFrameBuffer(frame);
479 return kNoError;
480 } else {
481 incomplete_frames_.InsertFrame(frame);
482 }
483 break;
484 }
485 case kNoError:
486 case kOutOfBoundsPacket:
487 case kDuplicatePacket: {
488 // Put back the frame where it came from.
489 if (frame_list != NULL) {
490 frame_list->InsertFrame(frame);
491 } else {
492 RecycleFrameBuffer(frame);
493 }
494 ++num_duplicated_packets_;
495 break;
496 }
497 case kFlushIndicator:
498 RecycleFrameBuffer(frame);
499 return kFlushIndicator;
500 default:
501 assert(false);
502 }
503 return buffer_state;
504}
505
506bool VCMJitterBuffer::IsContinuousInState(
507 const VCMFrameBuffer& frame,
508 const VCMDecodingState& decoding_state) const {
509 // Is this frame complete and continuous?
510 return (frame.GetState() == kStateComplete) &&
511 decoding_state.ContinuousFrame(&frame);
512}
513
514bool VCMJitterBuffer::IsContinuous(const VCMFrameBuffer& frame) const {
515 if (IsContinuousInState(frame, last_decoded_state_)) {
516 return true;
517 }
518 VCMDecodingState decoding_state;
519 decoding_state.CopyFrom(last_decoded_state_);
520 for (FrameList::const_iterator it = decodable_frames_.begin();
521 it != decodable_frames_.end(); ++it) {
522 VCMFrameBuffer* decodable_frame = it->second;
523 if (IsNewerTimestamp(decodable_frame->Timestamp(), frame.Timestamp())) {
524 break;
525 }
526 decoding_state.SetState(decodable_frame);
527 if (IsContinuousInState(frame, decoding_state)) {
528 return true;
529 }
530 }
531 return false;
532}
533
534void VCMJitterBuffer::FindAndInsertContinuousFrames(
535 const VCMFrameBuffer& new_frame) {
536 VCMDecodingState decoding_state;
537 decoding_state.CopyFrom(last_decoded_state_);
538 decoding_state.SetState(&new_frame);
539 FindAndInsertContinuousFramesWithState(decoding_state);
540}
541
542void VCMJitterBuffer::FindAndInsertContinuousFramesWithState(
543 const VCMDecodingState& original_decoded_state) {
544 // Copy original_decoded_state so we can move the state forward with each
545 // decodable frame we find.
546 VCMDecodingState decoding_state;
547 decoding_state.CopyFrom(original_decoded_state);
548
549 // When temporal layers are available, we search for a complete or decodable
550 // frame until we hit one of the following:
551 // 1. Continuous base or sync layer.
552 // 2. The end of the list was reached.
553 for (FrameList::iterator it = incomplete_frames_.begin();
554 it != incomplete_frames_.end();) {
555 VCMFrameBuffer* frame = it->second;
556 if (IsNewerTimestamp(original_decoded_state.time_stamp(),
557 frame->Timestamp())) {
558 ++it;
559 continue;
560 }
561 if (IsContinuousInState(*frame, decoding_state)) {
562 decodable_frames_.InsertFrame(frame);
563 incomplete_frames_.erase(it++);
564 decoding_state.SetState(frame);
565 } else if (frame->TemporalId() <= 0) {
566 break;
567 } else {
568 ++it;
569 }
570 }
571}

573uint32_t VCMJitterBuffer::EstimatedJitterMs() {
574 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
575 const double rtt_mult = 1.0f;
576 return jitter_estimate_.GetJitterEstimate(rtt_mult, absl::nullopt);
577}

579void VCMJitterBuffer::SetNackSettings(size_t max_nack_list_size,
580 int max_packet_age_to_nack,
581 int max_incomplete_time_ms) {
582 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
583 assert(max_packet_age_to_nack >= 0);
584 assert(max_incomplete_time_ms_ >= 0);
585 max_nack_list_size_ = max_nack_list_size;
586 max_packet_age_to_nack_ = max_packet_age_to_nack;
587 max_incomplete_time_ms_ = max_incomplete_time_ms;
588}
589
590int VCMJitterBuffer::NonContinuousOrIncompleteDuration() {
591 if (incomplete_frames_.empty()) {
592 return 0;
593 }
594 uint32_t start_timestamp = incomplete_frames_.Front()->Timestamp();
595 if (!decodable_frames_.empty()) {
596 start_timestamp = decodable_frames_.Back()->Timestamp();
597 }
598 return incomplete_frames_.Back()->Timestamp() - start_timestamp;
599}
600
601uint16_t VCMJitterBuffer::EstimatedLowSequenceNumber(
602 const VCMFrameBuffer& frame) const {
603 assert(frame.GetLowSeqNum() >= 0);
604 if (frame.HaveFirstPacket())
605 return frame.GetLowSeqNum();
606
607 // This estimate is not accurate if more than one packet with lower sequence
608 // number is lost.
609 return frame.GetLowSeqNum() - 1;
610}
611
612std::vector<uint16_t> VCMJitterBuffer::GetNackList(bool* request_key_frame) {
613 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
614 *request_key_frame = false;
615 if (last_decoded_state_.in_initial_state()) {
616 VCMFrameBuffer* next_frame = NextFrame();
617 const bool first_frame_is_key =
618 next_frame &&
619 next_frame->FrameType() == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey &&
620 next_frame->HaveFirstPacket();
621 if (!first_frame_is_key) {
622 bool have_non_empty_frame =
623 decodable_frames_.end() != find_if(decodable_frames_.begin(),
624 decodable_frames_.end(),
625 HasNonEmptyState);
626 if (!have_non_empty_frame) {
627 have_non_empty_frame =
628 incomplete_frames_.end() != find_if(incomplete_frames_.begin(),
629 incomplete_frames_.end(),
630 HasNonEmptyState);
631 }
632 bool found_key_frame = RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame();
633 if (!found_key_frame) {
634 *request_key_frame = have_non_empty_frame;
635 return std::vector<uint16_t>();
636 }
637 }
638 }
639 if (TooLargeNackList()) {
640 *request_key_frame = !HandleTooLargeNackList();
641 }
642 if (max_incomplete_time_ms_ > 0) {
643 int non_continuous_incomplete_duration =
644 NonContinuousOrIncompleteDuration();
645 if (non_continuous_incomplete_duration > 90 * max_incomplete_time_ms_) {
646 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "Too long non-decodable duration: "
647 << non_continuous_incomplete_duration << " > "
648 << 90 * max_incomplete_time_ms_;
649 FrameList::reverse_iterator rit = find_if(
650 incomplete_frames_.rbegin(), incomplete_frames_.rend(), IsKeyFrame);
651 if (rit == incomplete_frames_.rend()) {
652 // Request a key frame if we don't have one already.
653 *request_key_frame = true;
654 return std::vector<uint16_t>();
655 } else {
656 // Skip to the last key frame. If it's incomplete we will start
657 // NACKing it.
658 // Note that the estimated low sequence number is correct for VP8
659 // streams because only the first packet of a key frame is marked.
660 last_decoded_state_.Reset();
661 DropPacketsFromNackList(EstimatedLowSequenceNumber(*rit->second));
662 }
663 }
664 }
665 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_list(missing_sequence_numbers_.begin(),
666 missing_sequence_numbers_.end());
667 return nack_list;
668}
669
670VCMFrameBuffer* VCMJitterBuffer::NextFrame() const {
671 if (!decodable_frames_.empty())
672 return decodable_frames_.Front();
673 if (!incomplete_frames_.empty())
674 return incomplete_frames_.Front();
675 return NULL;
676}
677
678bool VCMJitterBuffer::UpdateNackList(uint16_t sequence_number) {
679 // Make sure we don't add packets which are already too old to be decoded.
680 if (!last_decoded_state_.in_initial_state()) {
681 latest_received_sequence_number_ = LatestSequenceNumber(
682 latest_received_sequence_number_, last_decoded_state_.sequence_num());
683 }
684 if (IsNewerSequenceNumber(sequence_number,
685 latest_received_sequence_number_)) {
686 // Push any missing sequence numbers to the NACK list.
687 for (uint16_t i = latest_received_sequence_number_ + 1;
688 IsNewerSequenceNumber(sequence_number, i); ++i) {
689 missing_sequence_numbers_.insert(missing_sequence_numbers_.end(), i);
690 }
691 if (TooLargeNackList() && !HandleTooLargeNackList()) {
692 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Requesting key frame due to too large NACK list.";
693 return false;
694 }
695 if (MissingTooOldPacket(sequence_number) &&
696 !HandleTooOldPackets(sequence_number)) {
697 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
698 << "Requesting key frame due to missing too old packets";
699 return false;
700 }
701 } else {
702 missing_sequence_numbers_.erase(sequence_number);
703 }
704 return true;
705}
706
707bool VCMJitterBuffer::TooLargeNackList() const {
708 return missing_sequence_numbers_.size() > max_nack_list_size_;
709}
710
711bool VCMJitterBuffer::HandleTooLargeNackList() {
712 // Recycle frames until the NACK list is small enough. It is likely cheaper to
713 // request a key frame than to retransmit this many missing packets.
714 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "NACK list has grown too large: "
715 << missing_sequence_numbers_.size() << " > "
716 << max_nack_list_size_;
717 bool key_frame_found = false;
718 while (TooLargeNackList()) {
719 key_frame_found = RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame();
720 }
721 return key_frame_found;
722}
723
724bool VCMJitterBuffer::MissingTooOldPacket(
725 uint16_t latest_sequence_number) const {
726 if (missing_sequence_numbers_.empty()) {
727 return false;
728 }
729 const uint16_t age_of_oldest_missing_packet =
730 latest_sequence_number - *missing_sequence_numbers_.begin();
731 // Recycle frames if the NACK list contains too old sequence numbers as
732 // the packets may have already been dropped by the sender.
733 return age_of_oldest_missing_packet > max_packet_age_to_nack_;
734}
735
736bool VCMJitterBuffer::HandleTooOldPackets(uint16_t latest_sequence_number) {
737 bool key_frame_found = false;
738 const uint16_t age_of_oldest_missing_packet =
739 latest_sequence_number - *missing_sequence_numbers_.begin();
740 RTC_LOG_F(LS_WARNING) << "NACK list contains too old sequence numbers: "
741 << age_of_oldest_missing_packet << " > "
742 << max_packet_age_to_nack_;
743 while (MissingTooOldPacket(latest_sequence_number)) {
744 key_frame_found = RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame();
745 }
746 return key_frame_found;
747}
748
749void VCMJitterBuffer::DropPacketsFromNackList(
750 uint16_t last_decoded_sequence_number) {
751 // Erase all sequence numbers from the NACK list which we won't need any
752 // longer.
753 missing_sequence_numbers_.erase(
754 missing_sequence_numbers_.begin(),
755 missing_sequence_numbers_.upper_bound(last_decoded_sequence_number));
756}
757
758VCMFrameBuffer* VCMJitterBuffer::GetEmptyFrame() {
759 if (free_frames_.empty()) {
760 if (!TryToIncreaseJitterBufferSize()) {
761 return NULL;
762 }
763 }
764 VCMFrameBuffer* frame = free_frames_.front();
765 free_frames_.pop_front();
766 return frame;
767}
768
769bool VCMJitterBuffer::TryToIncreaseJitterBufferSize() {
770 if (max_number_of_frames_ >= kMaxNumberOfFrames)
771 return false;
772 free_frames_.push_back(new VCMFrameBuffer());
773 ++max_number_of_frames_;
774 return true;
775}
776
777// Recycle oldest frames up to a key frame, used if jitter buffer is completely
778// full.
779bool VCMJitterBuffer::RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame() {
780 // First release incomplete frames, and only release decodable frames if there
781 // are no incomplete ones.
782 FrameList::iterator key_frame_it;
783 bool key_frame_found = false;
784 int dropped_frames = 0;
785 dropped_frames += incomplete_frames_.RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame(
786 &key_frame_it, &free_frames_);
787 key_frame_found = key_frame_it != incomplete_frames_.end();
788 if (dropped_frames == 0) {
789 dropped_frames += decodable_frames_.RecycleFramesUntilKeyFrame(
790 &key_frame_it, &free_frames_);
791 key_frame_found = key_frame_it != decodable_frames_.end();
792 }
793 if (key_frame_found) {
794 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Found key frame while dropping frames.";
795 // Reset last decoded state to make sure the next frame decoded is a key
796 // frame, and start NACKing from here.
797 last_decoded_state_.Reset();
798 DropPacketsFromNackList(EstimatedLowSequenceNumber(*key_frame_it->second));
799 } else if (decodable_frames_.empty()) {
800 // All frames dropped. Reset the decoding state and clear missing sequence
801 // numbers as we're starting fresh.
802 last_decoded_state_.Reset();
803 missing_sequence_numbers_.clear();
804 }
805 return key_frame_found;
806}
807
808void VCMJitterBuffer::UpdateAveragePacketsPerFrame(int current_number_packets) {
809 if (frame_counter_ > kFastConvergeThreshold) {
810 average_packets_per_frame_ =
811 average_packets_per_frame_ * (1 - kNormalConvergeMultiplier) +
812 current_number_packets * kNormalConvergeMultiplier;
813 } else if (frame_counter_ > 0) {
814 average_packets_per_frame_ =
815 average_packets_per_frame_ * (1 - kFastConvergeMultiplier) +
816 current_number_packets * kFastConvergeMultiplier;
817 frame_counter_++;
818 } else {
819 average_packets_per_frame_ = current_number_packets;
820 frame_counter_++;
821 }
822}
823
824// Must be called under the critical section |mutex_|.
825void VCMJitterBuffer::CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames() {
826 decodable_frames_.CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames(&last_decoded_state_,
827 &free_frames_);
828 incomplete_frames_.CleanUpOldOrEmptyFrames(&last_decoded_state_,
829 &free_frames_);
830 if (!last_decoded_state_.in_initial_state()) {
831 DropPacketsFromNackList(last_decoded_state_.sequence_num());
832 }
833}
834
835// Must be called from within |mutex_|.
836bool VCMJitterBuffer::IsPacketRetransmitted(const VCMPacket& packet) const {
837 return missing_sequence_numbers_.find(packet.seqNum) !=
838 missing_sequence_numbers_.end();
839}
840
841// Must be called under the critical section |mutex_|. Should never be
842// called with retransmitted frames, they must be filtered out before this
843// function is called.
844void VCMJitterBuffer::UpdateJitterEstimate(const VCMJitterSample& sample,
845 bool incomplete_frame) {
846 if (sample.latest_packet_time == -1) {
847 return;
848 }
849 UpdateJitterEstimate(sample.latest_packet_time, sample.timestamp,
850 sample.frame_size, incomplete_frame);
851}
852
853// Must be called under the critical section mutex_. Should never be
854// called with retransmitted frames, they must be filtered out before this
855// function is called.
856void VCMJitterBuffer::UpdateJitterEstimate(const VCMFrameBuffer& frame,
857 bool incomplete_frame) {
858 if (frame.LatestPacketTimeMs() == -1) {
859 return;
860 }
861 // No retransmitted frames should be a part of the jitter
862 // estimate.
863 UpdateJitterEstimate(frame.LatestPacketTimeMs(), frame.Timestamp(),
864 frame.size(), incomplete_frame);
865}
866
867// Must be called under the critical section |mutex_|. Should never be
868// called with retransmitted frames, they must be filtered out before this
869// function is called.
870void VCMJitterBuffer::UpdateJitterEstimate(int64_t latest_packet_time_ms,
871 uint32_t timestamp,
872 unsigned int frame_size,
873 bool incomplete_frame) {
874 if (latest_packet_time_ms == -1) {
875 return;
876 }
877 int64_t frame_delay;
878 bool not_reordered = inter_frame_delay_.CalculateDelay(
879 timestamp, &frame_delay, latest_packet_time_ms);
880 // Filter out frames which have been reordered in time by the network
881 if (not_reordered) {
882 // Update the jitter estimate with the new samples
883 jitter_estimate_.UpdateEstimate(frame_delay, frame_size, incomplete_frame);
884 }
885}
886
887void VCMJitterBuffer::RecycleFrameBuffer(VCMFrameBuffer* frame) {
888 frame->Reset();
889 free_frames_.push_back(frame);
890}
